values:
How to make a SolareYe9_2K4
Ingredients:
3 parts competetiveness
5 parts crazyiness
1 part ego
Method:
Blend at a low speed for 30 seconds. Add lovability to taste! Do not overindulge!

Username:

Personality cocktail
From Go-Quiz.com Hmmm...Interesting....

What was this Holiday meant for? To make people who have no love life what-so-ever like myself feel even more fucking depressed about their life? Hell, I don't even have any friends to spend the day with...EVERYONE I KNOW HAS FUCKING PLANS.

Somebody please shoot me in the fuckin' head one day.

Out.

Yeah I have a job. I've had one for a few days now. I work at Walmart, isn't that nice? We are about to open...tomorrow.

So, soon I shall have money.

And all will be well in the world....

That is all.

Saturday had a good show, wrestled under a mask for the 2ND TIME! :)

Saw Alex in his slumber...very funny sight, by-the-way Chellie I was the one that let Alex know we got pictures!

After the show got chopped and whipped for my birthday (masochistic bastards)...not to mention I think I about DIED when Jeff chopped me with his Hand of Death.

Yeah I'm 21 now and I can legally buy and drink alchohol. Too bad I don't have the money to do either...:(

Sunday woke up...tried to have a good birthday, but yet again couldn't have one without alot of pointless drama. Very irritating, but we all tried to have as much fun as we could with what we were given.

Monday, hoped I would receive a call about a job I intreviewed for last week, course didn't hear shit, and thus put me in one of those moods.

Besides that my life is FINE....(note the sarcasm)

Oh well, my life COULD be WORSE after-all....

Later, hopefully I will update this thing sooner next time.

And for once I've absolutely nothing to do...on a Saturday night!

But, yet I find myself anticipating the next show for that very reason...because I had nothing to really do tonight.

Next week we will be in Lincolnton which I prefer because that means I will get some training in hopefully.

And...I love training.

More than anything.

Okay that last statement was a lie, there are a few things I think I'd enjoy more than training...

Check the last post for more clarification on what I meant by "few things".

But anyway, as I said at the beginning, it's the first time in three weeks I've been home to catch some Adult Swim on a Saturday...eat some Ice Cream and just sit back and relax.

I saw Spiderman 2 with my dad last Wednesday. Pretty damn good movie.
I also got a new CD Wednesday..."The End of Heartache" by Killswitch Engage. Pretty fuckin' good CD.

Last few days, me and my ex...a.k.a. Shaina have been getting along again. Too bad her OTHER ex is back and seems to have found a way to get involved with friends she knows from work. I really feel bad for her cause it has taken a LONG time for her to get over him, and just when she is making alot of new friends, he pops back up and sticks his nose into her business as if he THINKS she would be happy to see him again after what happened between them. Oh, well...not much I can do but listen to her problems when she needs me too.

Me and my dad have been getting along fine aswell. But my mom and me got into a bad fight today. Makes me wish I had a job and could move out...maybe then I could finally get along with my parents.

Haven't been to a good party lately.

Man...I need to get drunk.

Counting down 'till September 12th. That day will be the day I turn 21 and can buy my own booze...and enjoy the freedom's....I've been enjoying since I joined the MWF.

Oh well, atleast I wont have to bum alchohol from other people ANYMORE...
I just hope I will actually have some money to buy booze with!

Well, that's enough of an update for you Solar Addicts(yeah all two of you!) for now...

'Till thy NEXT entry...
Whenever the hell that will be.

LATER!
If there is someone on your friends list you would love to have an epic, sweaty, damn near legendary, 12 hour fuckathon with, post this same exact sentence in your journal.

Yep boredom has struck this Solar System.

Nothing really good is going on today.

Just me, myself, and BOREDOM!!

Hmmm...I wish I had something more exciting to write about, but alas...I don't.

Can't wait till, the next MWF Show...which will be *GASP*....THIS WEEKEND!!! 2 WEEK'S IN A ROW!!

So, every single Solar Addict (All two of you!) better show up at the next show to support your Hypothesis of True Greatness as I kick someon-...errr...wait, I'm only a ref, so ummmm...

Show up and watch them call me ducky, and ref chuck and stuff...heh.

Maybe I'll print some flyers out for the next show. That is atleast SOMETHING to do!

Well I think I will end this entry right here...

Till Another Time...and Another Entry...

May thy BOREDOM Continue!

Later!

The show went well, except for the fact that we only drew like 62 people...which SUCKS! Oh well I know the quality of the show we produced wasn't the reason our attendence was down that's for sure. "Outlaw" Keith Matthews paid for a ticket and managed to cost Justin Sayne the MWF Title even though Outlaw was "Fired"....lol, I accidently got a foot to the face from our MWF Champ Scott St. James, and before that me and Shaina annoyed the hell out of eachother trying to talk the other into finishing an MWF Banner I...err...I mean WE were supposed to make ;)~...lol.

Besides that everything is the same as always, nothing much is different.

Today's been pretty boring. But atleast I have the next show to look forward to, and hopefully some fun after when JD has one of his famous "MWF After Party's" after the next show!

Oh well, things aren't the best still, I still want a job but can't find one, I still want a liscence but can't get one, and I still want a girlfriend but don't know enough girls! lol...

Well that's enough from me for now, till my next entry in this crazy Journal thingie!

Later!

Welcome Solar Addict's to the first entry of my *New*...JOURNAL!!

Anyway's, my name is Chris Baldwin. I have many alias'...such as Chris Solar (the Wrestling character I want to one day wrestle as...), Chuck (the nickname given to me by my trainer in the MWF, and thus causing hardly anyone to remember my real name is Chris! LoL), and plenty of others I don't wish to name as of right now.

Yeah as you can probally guess I hate doing intro's...

Ummm, let's see I love wrestling which is why I am training to be one, even if I don't ever make money at it like the big wigs in the WWE do, I don't really care, I wrestle for the fun of it...but untill I'm ready, I somehow managed to weasel into the show as a ref for now! LoL...

I'm normally a shy person till you get to know me, then you can't shut me up! Because of that reason, I haven't dated too many girls...ok, I dated only one girl but hey atleast I managed to avoid the post breakup curse, and stayed friends with the girl I had dated...even if we tend to get on eachothers nerves quite alot!

I also am a big videogame nerd...or dork...whatever term you wish to use, probally fits me very easily! I just got into anime again, and thus I'm pretty into shows like InuYasha, Trigun, Cowboy BeBop, FLCL, and Case Closed.

My choice of music is Rock music definently...if it has a guitar, bass, drums in it...more than likely I will like what I hear. ;)~

I have another journal with alot of older entries in it...

If you want read those go to the old journal at...http://www.blurty.com/users/solareye9

Unlike most people I intend on keeping up with both journals...so from here on out if I post something in this journal I will post it in my other one as well...

So with that said...this long ass intro is finally done with, good riddance!

I'm Out.

Later!
